(3834, 22, 'contact_description', 'The VHIO Academy manages the VIDA Programme and has in place a devoted Helpdesk &amp; Technical Support Service that will be active throughout the duration of the programme.\r\n\r\nCandidates are encouraged to contact the Helpdesk service via email to solve any questions or issues regarding the application &amp; selection process.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>The VHIO Academy</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe VHIO Academy mission is to boost the careers of biomedical, pre-clinical and translational oncology researchers by providing advanced training, support and guidance along their scientific path at VHIO.\r\n\r\nOur main objectives are:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Develop cancer-focused <u>educational programs</u> and manage <u>mentoring and training</u> activities to help VHIO members further their education and careers, as well as foster a training environment of excellence.</li>\r\n 	<li>Launch and manage<u> academic programs at all levels</u> to reinforce the international attraction strategy of talented professionals.</li>\r\n 	<li><u>Increase and consolidate collaborations</u> with Comprehensive Cancer Centers (CCCs) and international cancer research consortia to further expand educational activities, network of collaborators, as well as foster the mobility of researchers and clinicians at international level.</li>\r\n 	<li>Establish <u>new initiatives</u> to strengthen and reinforce the sense of belonging to the VHIO community.</li>\r\n 	<li>Reinforce internal &amp; external <u>scientific communication and dissemination</u> of cancer research findings.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;'),
